at 4\u00b0C until testing. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">8. Conduct testing within 4 hours.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1083611,"guid":"4A7633B032D711EB89ECC10A65F81F1F","previous_id":1083609,"previous_guid":"8C5BEE7032D511EB993495E7101FAF62","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E004717E8F734A77A6E547779616A85F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prepare triaxial machine for testing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9E53CFCDEE1241FF9336C669A713A6BD","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">1. Fill tank and inflation liquid bottle with Ca-free Kreb.<\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><span>2. Open the 95% O<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> \u2013 5% CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><span>line to aerate the Ca-free Kreb solution.<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">3. Turn on the heater (setup for 37C) and the associate pump.<\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">4. Setup a pH-meter to monitor pH. Make sure pH = 7.4\u00b10.1 before starting the test. Adjust pH if necessary.<\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">5. Calibrate camera using the known diameter of the tissue holder.<\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">6. Open main pressure valve. Open machine pressure valve to let Ca-free Kreb flow through and remove any air.<\/div><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1083612,"guid":"1653AF8032D811EB89ECC10A65F81F1F","previous_id":1083611,"previous_guid":"4A7633B032D711EB89ECC10A65F81F1F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5D15F86A953A43D889074C59144377E5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prepare tissue for testing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BDD72816566744149652DC84DC5A8EDD","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">1. Take tissue out of the storage solution and dissect connective tissues and major mesentery vessels.<\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">2. Mount the tissue on the triaxial machine and secure it with O-rings. <\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">3. Open exhaust bolt on the tissue mount, then open the pressure valve and let solution flow through the tissue and out of the exhaust. <\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">4. Close pressure valve and the exhaust bolt. <\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">5. Once bath temperature is at 37C, start the test.<\/div><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1083613,"guid":"C9AFD2C032D811EB89ECC10A65F81F1F","previous_id":1083612,"previous_guid":"1653AF8032D811EB89ECC10A65F81F1F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D4A043A155014FCA80939338F733F3DD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Conduct testing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C0ED78ED3DD14CF9BE157E6ADAB10E9E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">1. Stretch the tissue back-end forth up to a 40% stretch five times while maintaining tissue pressure at 0.5 kPa and 0 twist.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2. At multiples stretch steps where the tissue is not bulging, inflate-deflate the tissue back and forth four times between 0.5 and 2 kPa while maintaining the tissue at 0 twist.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. At multiples stretch steps where the tissue is not bulging and at multiple pressure steps between 0.5 and 2 kPa, twist the tissue back and forth four times between -40 and 40 degrees.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol describes the step followed to conduct ex vivo triaxial mechanical testing (inflation, extension, torsion) of dog colon samples on our custom build testing platform. <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1611603679}